6:
What a sight! A beach as far as the
eye can see! Now this feels like
another world. I can feel my very
soul tingling!
10:
It ain't no beach. It's just sand. That's
it.
14:
Details, details. But never mind that.
THIS is what I'm here for!
17:
According to the ancient texts I
found, there should be ruins and
treasure somewhere in this area.
22:
The ruins are supposed to be where
this mark is, right? What's this writing
here?
26:
Those are ancient glyphs.
"Those who seek the light of the
ruins, jump readily into the seas of
sand."
30:
Wow! What about this part? What
does it say?
34:
Who knows? I didn't bother to
decipher it.
41:
Come on now, what's an adventure
without a little dose of the unknown?
It's more thrilling this way.
46:
Hey... Are you trying to get us killed
or something?
50: "Us"? Are you guys coming with me?
55:
Well, letting you go alone at this rate
feels irresponsible.
59:
Yeah, something tells me you won't
last long without us...
62: What? You got a problem with that?
67:
No... I was wondering how you
softies wound up with such weird
taste in friends and activities.
71:
Well, in that case, I welcome you to
Marcus' Grand Tour of Thrills!
76:
I'd prefer a thrill-free tour myself, but
I don't think that's gonna happen.
80:
According to the map, the ruins
should be around here... But I see no
structures of any kind.
84:
Maybe that map's a fake? Or the
ruins are long gone.
90:
No... My gut's telling me this is the
place. I can practically smell the
adventures waiting for us!
94:
Here comes the welcoming
committee. Unfortunately for them,
they caught me in a thrill-seeking
mood!
104:
Crud, quicksand! Get away from
there!
108:
The hell are you doing?! You're
gonna get sucked in!
113:
"Jump readily into the seas of sand,"
was it? All right, have it your way!
123: You've got to be kidding me!
130:
Look who decided to tag along.
Guess you've got an eye for
adventure yourself.
135:
Yeah, right! You jumped into that
quicksand, so I followed you in to
save your ass! What else was I
supposed to do?
139:
All right, all right, calm down. There's
adrenaline-pumping thrills ahead of
us, so why don't we try to enjoy them?
144:
Wait, don't touch that! Treasure
wouldn't be out here in the open!
148:
So you think it's a trap? ...Good eye.
You’ve got the makings of a great
thrill seeker.
158:
Ha, a trigger, huh? Now things are
getting interesting!
164:
Remind me to give you a good slug
later!
168: Tch! How many of these are there?!
177:
These guardians are set to protect
these ruins! They will continue their
pursuit of you until you let go of the
device!
181: Where did you guys come from?!
186:
We took a shortcut. It was written in
the ancient texts.
191:
Wait, you deciphered the rest of the
glyphs?! I should make you my
sidekick!
196:
Now is not the time for wisecracks!
The glyphs she deciphered read,
"Should the light of the ruins be lost,
all will return to the sands!"
201:
Oh, so we just gotta get out of here
before the ruins collapse!
206:
What?! No! You have to put that
thing back!
212:
Urgh... We mustn't dally here!
Quickly, to the exit!
221:
*sigh* Looks like this adventure must
come to an end.
225:
Thanks for the thrills. It was fun while
it lasted!
240:
Man, the ruins sure are... in ruin. That
treasure's long gone now.
244:
Yeah, but if you hadn't returned it,
we probably would've been buried
alive along with it.
249:
You know, you probably could've
gotten away with the treasure if you
just left us there.
254:
I suppose I could've... But it doesn't
matter. It's the thrills and adventure
I'm after.
257:
Besides, who needs treasure when
you've got friends like these?
262:
Ha. With a friend like you, who needs
enemies?
266:
Anyway, I'm sure we'll find even
better ruins in the future.
271:
While I certainly don't mind such
expeditions... I ask that you at least
fully decipher any glyphs
beforehand.
275:
Ah, right... Guess I'll be calling on you
for help, Stella.
